# Version bump — BC / BCP

**Source of truth:** `VERSION` at the project root (`major`, `minor`, `bump` as `key=value`; display **X.Y.B**).

When the user message is **`BCP`** (Bump + Commit + Push):

1. Increment **`bump`** by 1 in `VERSION` (do not change `major` or `minor` unless the user asks).
2. Stage `VERSION` (and only other files if they are part of the same explicit release step).
3. Commit with a message like `bump version to X.Y.B` (use HEREDOC per git rules).
4. **`git push`** to remote.

When the user message is **`BC`** (Bump + Commit only):

1. Same bump in `VERSION`.
2. Commit only — **do not push**.

Treat **`BC`** / **`BCP`** as standalone commands (trimmed message, case-insensitive).

Follow all user git safety rules (no force push, no config changes, no amend unless allowed).

The in-game label reads `VERSION` via autoload `Version` on next run.
